RVS ATCT directly observes and has received multiple reports of UAS activity 1 NM SE of airport between 400-1100 AGL. No evasive action has been taken by aircraft, however the ATCT has modified their pattern traffic to avoid the unauthorized UAS activity. HQ DEN requested ATCT notify Airport Management and add unauthorized UAS activity to their ATIS as well as notify all arriving and departing aircraft. HQ DEN requested RVS ATCT notify local LEO. RVS ATCT advised Jenks County Sheriff notified at requesting to dispatch officer to locate operator and cease UAS operations impacting airport operations. RVS ATCT will continue to advise HQ DEN, TSOC informed via the DEN Bridge. 1905 CLOSEOUT: RVS ATCT advises HQ DEN that local Police Department was the operator of the UAS monitoring a festival in the local area. RVS ATCT has requested operations cease due to operational impacts. Dispatch relayed to operator, no further reports have been received and the UAS activity can no longer be directly observed. RVS ATCT advises they will return to normal operation when festival ends at 1930. NFA. AWO, JH notified.
